   <concept id="FAR_3_104_8" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">3.104-8</ph> Criminal and civil penalties, and further administrative remedies.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d98e8" class="- topic/p ">Criminal and civil penalties, and administrative remedies, may apply to conduct that violates <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid%3AUSC-prelim-title41-chapter21&amp;saved=%7CZ3JhbnVsZWlkOlVTQy1wcmVsaW0tdGl0bGU0MC1jaGFwdGVyMzctZnJvbnQ%3D%7C%7C%7C0%7Cfalse%7Cprelim&amp;edition=prelim"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">41 U.S.C. chapter 21</xref> (see <xref href="3.104-3.dita#FAR_3_104_3"
                  base="i1124784"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">3.104-3</xref>). See <xref href="33.102.dita#FAR_33_102"
                  base="i1080417"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">33.102</xref>(f) for special rules regarding bid protests. See <xref href="3.104-7.dita#FAR_3_104_7"
                  base="i1124936"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">3.104-7</xref> for administrative remedies relating to contracts.</p>
         <ol id="d96e40" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d98e24">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
						            An official who knowingly fails to comply with the requirements of <xref href="3.104-3.dita#FAR_3_104_3"
                        base="i1124784"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">3.104-3</xref> is subject to the penalties and administrative action set forth in <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section2105&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">41 U.S.C. 2105</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d98e35">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
						            An offeror who engages in employment discussion with an official subject to the restrictions of <xref href="3.104-3.dita#FAR_3_104_3"
                        base="i1124784"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">3.104-3</xref>, knowing that the official has not complied with <xref href="3.104-3.dita#FAR_3_104_3"
                        base="i1124784"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">3.104-3</xref>(c)(1), is subject to the criminal, civil, or administrative penalties set forth in <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title41-section2105&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">41 U.S.C. 2105</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d98e49">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
						            An official who refuses to terminate employment discussions (see <xref href="3.104-5.dita#FAR_3_104_5"
                        base="i1124883"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">3.104-5</xref>) may be subject to agency administrative actions under <ph outputclass="CFR" class="- topic/ph ">5 CFR 2635.604(d)</ph> if the official’s disqualification from participation in a particular procurement interferes substantially with the individual’s ability to perform assigned duties.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
